In a research project I am working on in a computational geometry setting, I have two classes of importance. One is what I call an `oriented_cell` class and the other is a `vertex` class. Both are currently templated with the following forward declarations:

    /* Forward declaration for the oriented cell class */
    template&lt;
       typename data_t,
       typename container,
       typename id_t   = uint32_t,
       typename num_t  = double &gt;
    class oriented_cell;

    /* Forward declaration for vertex class */
    template&lt;
       int dim = 4,
       typename id_t = uint32_t,
       typename num_t  = double &gt;
    class vertex;

Both of these templated classes require storing pointers to the other class such that I will end up with a type of graph data structure I can traverse. The sort of thing I am after is something along the lines of:

    // templated vertex class
    template&lt;
       int dim = 4,
       typename id_t = uint32_t,
       typename num_t  = double &gt;
    class vertex {
    public:
       /* ctors/dtors and public methods */
    private:
       std::set&lt; oriented_cell&lt;...&gt;* &gt; incident_cells;
    };
    
    // templated oriented cell class
    template&lt;
       typename data_t,
       typename container,
       typename id_t   = uint32_t,
       typename num_t  = double &gt;
    class oriented_cell {
    public:
       /* ctors/dtors and public methods */
    private:
       std::set&lt; vertex&lt;...&gt;* &gt; vertices;
    };

where `vertex&lt;...&gt;` and `oriented_cell&lt;...&gt;` correspond to arbitrary templated types of a `vertex` and `oriented_cell` class. 

Is this feasible? If so, how? I am not able to see how to implement this when the classes that are coupled on each other are templated. 

If this is not feasible as-is, is there something more elegant that achieves the desired result without resorting to making the two classes based on some shared base class that acts as a graph node that can store connectivity info?

